.image1{

width:50%;

height:50%;

display: block;

margin-left: auto;

margin-right: auto;

padding:5px;

background-color: black;

border-color:#999900;

border-width:2px;

border-style:solid;

}



Notes:
When you set the left and right margins to auto, that specifies that they should split the available margin space equally, 
and the result is a centered element.

content(image)-padding-border-margin
padding can be colored with the background-color.
